# Code Conventions

> Standards for consistent, maintainable code.

## Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Files | kebab-case | `user-service.ts` |
| Directories | kebab-case | `api-handlers/` |
| Variables | camelCase | `userName` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE | `MAX_RETRY_COUNT` |
| Functions | camelCase | `getUserById()` |
| Classes | PascalCase | `UserService` |
| Types/Interfaces | PascalCase | `UserConfig` |
| Enums | PascalCase | `UserStatus` |

## File Organization

### Project Structure

```
src/
├── components/     # UI components (if applicable)
├── services/       # Business logic
├── utils/          # Helper functions
├── types/          # Type definitions
├── constants/      # Shared constants
└── index.ts        # Public exports
```

### File Contents

- One primary export per file
- Keep files under 300 lines
- Group related functions together

## Code Style

### Formatting

| Element | Standard |
|---------|----------|
| Indentation | 2 spaces |
| Line length | 100 characters max |
| Quotes | Single quotes for strings |
| Semicolons | Consistent (use or don't use) |

### Comments

**DO comment:**
- Complex business logic
- Non-obvious decisions
- TODO items with context

**DON'T comment:**
- Obvious code (`i++; // increment i`)
- Dead code (delete instead)
- Change history (use git)

### Functions

- Keep functions under 50 lines
- Single responsibility
- Descriptive names over comments
- Early returns for guard clauses

## Git Conventions

### Commit Messages

Format: `type: short description`

| Type | Usage |
|------|-------|
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `refactor` | Code change without behavior change |
| `test` | Adding/modifying tests |
| `chore` | Maintenance, dependencies |

### Examples

```bash
feat: add user authentication
fix: resolve null pointer in login
docs: update API documentation
refactor: simplify validation logic
test: add unit tests for UserService
chore: update dependencies
```

### Branches

| Type | Format | Example |
|------|--------|---------|
| Feature | `feature/description` | `feature/add-auth` |
| Fix | `fix/description` | `fix/login-error` |
| Docs | `docs/description` | `docs/api-guide` |

## Dependencies

- Minimize external dependencies
- Document why each dependency is needed
- Keep dependencies updated
- Prefer well-maintained packages
